3. **[Paul Bunyan Statue](/Statue_of_Paul_Bunyan_(Portland,_Oregon))**  
   *More images*  
   **Date listed:** January 28, 2009 [&#93;]  
   **Location:** Corner of N Denver Avenue and N Interstate Avenue, coordinates 45°35′02″N 122°41′12″W / 45.583822°N 122.686594°W / 45.583822; ‑122.686594 [&#93;]  
   **Description:** This 31‑foot (9.4 m) sculpture of the folkloric logger **Paul Bunyan** in Portland’s **Kenton** neighborhood was erected in 1959 to commemorate the **centennial of Oregon's statehood** during the Centennial Exposition and International Trade Fair. Its steel skeleton and painted‑plaster detailing were fabricated by local firms, and its placement on Interstate Avenue marked the main northern gateway to the city. The work exemplifies 20th‑century novelty roadside architecture and reflects Oregon’s tradition of rugged individualism and its deep ties to the **timber industry** [Forest_product](/Forest_product) [8&#93;] [9&#93;].

